    &lt;Title&gt;Thank you&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Debbie&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;
 
 
I just wanted to write and thank you and the Good Care Company for the care that my parents have received over the last 4 and a bit years.  All of the carers looked after mum and dad in a kind and compassionate manner.  They treated both of them with respect and understanding.  The patience that was shown, especially towards dad was outstanding.  One Carer in particular was brilliant with dad and got him to understand about mums dementia and the best way for him to handle it. 
 
When dad passed away, mums care was exceptional.  I know we had some difficulties but these were always dealt with in a sympathetic manner and with a view to rectifying the problem whilst taking the familyâ€™s wishes into consideration. The care and attention that mum has received contributed greatly to her health and well being.  Whilst acknowledging her dementia she was always treated with respect and as an individual.  The three main Carers went out of their way to make sure that mum was always in a happy place and had the best care that they could possibly give. I must also thank the Carers for their care and sacrifices over the  last few months as the country dealt with covid.  In such a difficult time it was comforting knowing that mum was safe in their hands.  We as a family will never be able to thank them enough.  Mum spent her last few years knowing that she was cared for and loved.  We also learnt from the carers and it helped us to come to terms with mums condition and accept it.
 
I would thoroughly recommend the Good Care Company and again thank you both and all the carers for their hard work. 
 

